fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.mapdb.store

Class DirectWriteMapDbListsStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.store.AbstractPersistentStore
      • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.store.AbstractDirectWriteStore<MapDbPersistenceBackend>
        • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.mapdb.store.DirectWriteMapDbStore
          • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.data.mapdb.store.DirectWriteMapDbListsStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DirectWriteStore, PersistentStore, InternalEObject.EStore

    public class DirectWriteMapDbListsStore
extends DirectWriteMapDbStore
    A DirectWriteMapDbStore that uses Java Lists instead of arrays to persist multi-valued EAttributes and EReferences.

    Using a List-based implementation allows to benefit from the rich Java Collection API, with the cost of a small memory overhead compared to raw arrays.

    This class re-implements EStructuralFeature accessors and mutators as well as Collection operations such as size, clear, or indexOf.

    This store can be used as a base store that can be complemented by plugging decorator stores on top of it (see AbstractPersistentStoreDecorator subclasses) to provide additional features such as caching or logging.

    See Also:
    DirectWriteMapDbStore, MapDbPersistenceBackend, AbstractPersistentStoreDecorator
